    and t1_0.txn_date between ? and ?
... followed directly by 667 individual "insert into statement (...) values (...)"
statements — the read side collapsed to one query, the write side (row-by-row
save(), IDENTITY ids) is untouched; that's M7's variable, not this one.

Sanity counts across both runs:
  join-query occurrences (grep "^    join$")            -> 2  (exactly 1 per run)
  statement inserts (grep "into" + "statement")           -> 1334  (667 * 2 runs)
  query count per run: 1 (join query) + 667 (inserts) + 1 (run insert) + 1 (run update) = 670 -- matches jdbcQueryCount exactly.
